
Overview of noun halt

The noun halt has 3 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (1) arrest, check, halt, hitch, stay, stop, stoppage -- (the state of inactivity following an interruption; "the negotiations were in arrest"; "held them in check"; "during the halt he got some lunch"; "the momentary stay enabled him to escape the blow"; "he spent the entire stop in his seat")
2. (1) stop, halt -- (the event of something ending; "it came to a stop at the bottom of the hill")
3. (1) freeze, halt -- (an interruption or temporary suspension of progress or movement; "a halt in the arms race"; "a nuclear freeze")

